      "chunkId": "fever_guidelines#0",
      "sourceId": "fever_guidelines",
      "title": "fever_guidelines.md",
      "text": "# Fever (General Guidance)\n\nFever is often caused by infections, but the severity of symptoms and associated warning signs matter more than the exact number on a thermometer.\n\nSeek emergency care immediately if you have fever with any of the following:\n\n- trouble breathing, severe weakness, chest pain, confusion, fainting\n\n- stiff neck, new rash, or severe headache\n\n- seizure\n\nFor non-emergency cases:\n\n- Stay hydrated (small frequent sips of water or oral rehydration solution if tolerated).\n\n- Rest.\n\n- Consider checking temperature trends over time.\n\n- If you are immunocompromised, have significant chronic illness, are very young, or symptoms are worsening, seek urgent medical evaluation.",
      "metadata": {
        "category": "fever"
      },
